      • teardown

        public void teardown()
        This teardown method is important to avoid the static map instances created in these tests from interfering with the unit tests of other classes. This is important since most unit tests assume that "MapCreator" will always return the map instance that they requested. However, this may not be the case if the unit tests are not run in in order; for example, if a unit test from HTMLGeneratorTest is run right after one of the tests in this class.
